A) DOCKER
* docker rmi $(docker images -a -q)                 --> remove all images
* docker build -t <tag-name> .                      -—> create image
* docker run -p <out-port>:<in-port> <image-name>   -—> create and run new container regarding to selected image
* docker start <existed-container-name>             —-> start existed container with same parameters which used before


B) KUBERNATE
* kubectl apply -f rbac.yml        --> kubernate role binding
* kubectl apply -f deployment.yml  --> image deploment
* kubectl get pods                  --> watch deployment
* kubectl delete deployment <NAME>  --> delete existed deployment

